fix(services): :bug: handle null record in findById

Why:
UserService.findById() throws a null pointer exception when
querying for a user ID that does not exist in the database.
This crash silently fails the request handler and provides
no meaningful feedback to callers.

What:
Add null check after database query and return a proper error
response with descriptive message instead of throwing an
unhandled exception.

Ticket: PROJ-247
Signed-off-by: Alice Developer <alice@example.com>
